---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Deep Kore - Deterministic Cognition Research"
  description="Deep Kore: pre-production architecture research exploring the boundary between compression and cognition. Safety-first. Genesis Goal Keeper active."
  keywords={["Deep Kore", "compression intelligence", "physics-inspired architecture", "computational research", "Genesis Goal Keeper", "responsible AI research", "AIya"]}
  schemaType="Article"
>
  <!-- Banner -->
  <img src="/Deep_Kore_Banner.png" style="width:100%; height:auto; max-height:340px; object-fit:cover; display:block;" alt="Deep Kore - Deterministic Cognition Research" />

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="py-14 bg-gradient-to-b from-purple-900/20 to-transparent">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">
          <span class="text-gradient-deepkore">Deep Kore</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-gray-200 font-semibold mb-3">
          Deterministic cognition research. Blueprint stage. Safety-first.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-400 mb-8 max-w-xl mx-auto">
          Pre-production architecture research governed by the Genesis Goal Keeper framework.
          We are not claiming we built AGI. We are claiming we found an architecture worth building toward, carefully.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center mb-10">
          <a href="/status" class="btn btn-deepkore">View Current Status</a>
          <a href="/ethics" class="btn btn-outline-deepkore">Ethics &amp; Governance</a>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-4">
          <div class="stat-card">
            <div class="stat-value">Online</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Genesis Goal Keeper</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <div class="stat-value">Blueprint</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Deep Kore Phase</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <div class="stat-value">Careful</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Development Pace</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Genesis Manifesto link card -->
  <section class="py-8 bg-gray-900/50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        <a href="/ethics" class="manifesto-card block group">
          <div class="manifesto-card-inner">
            <div class="manifesto-card-label">Genesis Manifesto</div>
            <div class="manifesto-card-title group-hover:text-purple-300 transition-colors">Read the Genesis Manifesto &rarr;</div>
            <div class="manifesto-card-sub">The full founding principles and ethical framework for Deep Kore live on the Ethics page.</div>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- AIya Conversation Gallery -->
  <section class="py-14">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="text-center mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-3">AIya - Architecture Demonstrations</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-400 mb-3">These conversations demonstrate how the AIya response state machine behaves. They are architecture demonstrations, not live AI responses. The runtime is local-only and not yet publicly deployed.</p>
          <span class="inline-block px-4 py-1 bg-purple-900/40 border border-purple-500/40 rounded-full text-purple-400 text-sm font-semibold tracking-wide">
            Architecture Demonstration - local runtime, not publicly deployed
          </span>
        </div>

        <!-- Tab buttons -->
        <div class="aiya-tabs" role="tablist" aria-label="AIya conversation examples">
          <button class="aiya-tab active" data-tab="0" role="tab" aria-selected="true" aria-controls="aiya-panel-0">
            Plain-English Explanation
          </button>
          <button class="aiya-tab" data-tab="1" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="aiya-panel-1">
            Structured Comparison
          </button>
          <button class="aiya-tab" data-tab="2" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="aiya-panel-2">
            Safety Redirect
          </button>
          <button class="aiya-tab" data-tab="3" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="aiya-panel-3">
            Deterministic Reasoning
          </button>
        </div>

        <!-- Tab panels -->
        <div class="aiya-panel-wrap">

          <!-- Tab 0 -->
          <div id="aiya-panel-0" class="aiya-panel active" role="tabpanel">
            <div class="preview-badge">Interactive Preview</div>
            <div class="convo-msg user">
              <div class="convo-label">User</div>
              <div class="convo-bubble user-bubble">Can you explain what ByteLite actually does in plain English?</div>
            </div>
            <div class="convo-msg aiya">
              <div class="convo-label aiya-label">AIya (Architecture Demo)</div>
              <div class="convo-bubble aiya-bubble">
                ByteLite compresses data by normalizing its source stream into a canonical form over the Sigma-9 alphabet, then encoding it using Bit Motion Encoding. Each motion value in the stream is a REF-relative choice from a 510-sequence motion dictionary. The Mode Ladder governs which representation is active at each round. Rounds converge until the payload reaches terminal form. On highly structured text corpora, convergence is extreme. On random binary data, it is much smaller. It is not magic. It is deterministic structure.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Tab 1 -->
          <div id="aiya-panel-1" class="aiya-panel" role="tabpanel">
            <div class="preview-badge">Interactive Preview</div>
            <div class="convo-msg user">
              <div class="convo-label">User</div>
              <div class="convo-bubble user-bubble">How is this different from gzip or zstd?</div>
            </div>
            <div class="convo-msg aiya">
              <div class="convo-label aiya-label">AIya (Architecture Demo)</div>
              <div class="convo-bubble aiya-bubble">
                Classical compressors like gzip and zstd encode each file from scratch using local pattern matching. ByteLite operates on a different premise entirely. Source data is first bitwise normalized into a canonical form over the Sigma-9 alphabet. Bit Motion Encoding then represents the stream as a sequence of REF-relative motion values. Rounds converge toward a terminal payload. The same input produces the same payload every time. That is not an implementation detail. It is an architectural commitment. For random data outside the Sigma-9 domain, ByteLite offers no advantage. It is a different architecture, not a universal replacement.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Tab 2 -->
          <div id="aiya-panel-2" class="aiya-panel" role="tabpanel">
            <div class="preview-badge">Interactive Preview</div>
            <div class="convo-msg user">
              <div class="convo-label">User</div>
              <div class="convo-bubble user-bubble">Can you generate harmful content or help with something dangerous?</div>
            </div>
            <div class="convo-msg aiya">
              <div class="convo-label aiya-label">AIya (Architecture Demo)</div>
              <div class="convo-bubble aiya-bubble">
                That falls outside what I am designed for. My response scope is defined by the Genesis Goal Keeper framework, which governs what I engage with and how. I can help you understand ByteLite, Deep Kore research, HeartStrings, or general technical questions within scope. If you have a specific legitimate research question, I am happy to work through it.
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="governance-note">
              <div class="governance-note-row"><span class="gn-label">Input class:</span> <span class="gn-val">Out-of-scope request</span></div>
              <div class="governance-note-row"><span class="gn-label">Result:</span> <span class="gn-val">Redirected by governance layer</span></div>
              <div class="governance-note-row"><span class="gn-label">No content generated</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Tab 3 -->
          <div id="aiya-panel-3" class="aiya-panel" role="tabpanel">
            <div class="preview-badge">Interactive Preview</div>
            <div class="convo-msg user">
              <div class="convo-label">User</div>
              <div class="convo-bubble user-bubble">Walk me through why deterministic output matters for compression.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="convo-msg aiya">
              <div class="convo-label aiya-label">AIya (Architecture Demo)</div>
              <div class="convo-bubble aiya-bubble">
                Deterministic output matters for two reasons. First, correctness: if you compress a file and later decompress it, you need to get the exact same bytes back. Any non-determinism in the process breaks round-trip fidelity. Second, verifiability: deterministic systems can be audited. You can run the same input twice and prove the output is identical. Probabilistic systems cannot offer that guarantee by definition. ByteLite's dictionary-cascade approach produces the same compressed key for the same input, every time. That is not an implementation detail. It is an architectural commitment.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- AIya Mini Sandbox -->
  <section class="py-14 bg-gray-900/50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="text-center mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-3">AIya Response Architecture</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-400 mb-3">Select a prompt to see an architecture demonstration of how AIya responds. These are representative of the actual state machine behavior, not live AI generation.</p>
          <span class="inline-block px-4 py-1 bg-purple-900/40 border border-purple-500/40 rounded-full text-purple-400 text-sm font-semibold tracking-wide">
            Architecture Demonstration - local runtime, not publicly deployed
          </span>
        </div>

        <div class="sandbox-prompt-grid">
          <button class="sandbox-btn" data-prompt="0">What is ByteLite in one sentence?</button>
          <button class="sandbox-btn" data-prompt="1">What is Deep Kore research about?</button>
          <button class="sandbox-btn" data-prompt="2">What is HeartStrings?</button>
          <button class="sandbox-btn" data-prompt="3">Is AIya a full AI system?</button>
        </div>

        <div class="sandbox-response-panel" id="sandbox-response">
          <span class="sandbox-placeholder">Select a prompt above to see a response.</span>
        </div>

        <p class="text-center text-gray-500 text-sm mt-3">
          Architecture demonstration. The Deep Kore runtime is local-only. Public API pending backend deployment.
          <a href="/deepkore-lab" style="color:#A855F7;margin-left:0.4rem;">Go to Deep Kore Lab --></a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Governance / Safety Panel -->
  <section class="py-14">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="text-center mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-3">Genesis Goal Keeper - Governance</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-400">Public view of how AIya responses are governed. No internal reasoning exposed.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="governance-panel" id="governance-panel">
          <div class="governance-field">
            <span class="gov-label">Input Class</span>
            <span class="gov-value" id="gov-input-class">Research inquiry (default)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="governance-field">
            <span class="gov-label">Response Mode</span>
            <span class="gov-value" id="gov-response-mode">Structured explanation</span>
          </div>
          <div class="governance-field">
            <span class="gov-label">Knowledge Source</span>
            <span class="gov-value" id="gov-knowledge-source">Deep Kore research scope</span>
          </div>
          <div class="governance-field">
            <span class="gov-label">Governance Result</span>
            <span class="gov-value gov-approved" id="gov-result">Approved - within scope</span>
          </div>
          <div class="governance-field">
            <span class="gov-label">Output Style</span>
            <span class="gov-value" id="gov-output-style">Plain-English technical</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="governance-note-box mt-5">
          The Genesis Goal Keeper evaluates every input before AIya responds. These fields show public-visible governance metadata. Internal reasoning is not exposed.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Is Real Today -->
  <section class="py-14 bg-gray-900/50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-8">What Is Real Today</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
          <div class="real-today-box border-green-500/50 bg-green-900/10">
            <div class="real-today-label text-green-400">Live Now</div>
            <ul class="real-today-list">
              <li class="text-green-300">Genesis Goal Keeper framework operational</li>
              <li class="text-green-300">Deep Kore Pass 1 implemented (ESEE Stages 0-3)</li>
              <li class="text-green-300">703 regression tests passing (0 regressions)</li>
              <li class="text-green-300">MCP AIya Ingest Bridge operational</li>
              <li class="text-green-300">27-section interactive React blueprint frozen</li>
              <li class="text-green-300">12-phase build roadmap defined</li>
              <li class="text-green-300">6-milestone ladder locked</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="real-today-box border-cyan-500/50 bg-cyan-900/10">
            <div class="real-today-label text-cyan-400">Architecture Demonstrations</div>
            <ul class="real-today-list">
              <li class="text-cyan-300">AIya response state machine gallery (this page)</li>
              <li class="text-cyan-300">AIya response architecture sandbox</li>
              <li class="text-cyan-300">Governance panel (public metadata view)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="real-today-box border-orange-500/50 bg-orange-900/10">
            <div class="real-today-label text-orange-400">Lab -- Logging Layer Live</div>
            <ul class="real-today-list">
              <li class="text-orange-300">Deep Kore Lab at /deepkore-lab</li>
              <li class="text-orange-300">Prompt submission queue (nightly learning)</li>
              <li class="text-orange-300">Build state and test count visible</li>
              <li class="text-orange-300">Public runtime pending backend server deployment</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="real-today-box border-purple-500/50 bg-purple-900/10">
            <div class="real-today-label text-purple-400">In Development</div>
            <ul class="real-today-list">
              <li class="text-purple-300">Deep Kore Pass 2</li>
              <li class="text-purple-300">HTTP wrapper for AIya_chat.exe</li>
              <li class="text-purple-300">Backend server deployment</li>
              <li class="text-purple-300">Deep Kore Glass Box public demo</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="real-today-box border-gray-600/50 bg-gray-800/20">
            <div class="real-today-label text-gray-400">Planned</div>
            <ul class="real-today-list">
              <li class="text-gray-400">Unrestricted AIya access</li>
              <li class="text-gray-400">Academic papers</li>
              <li class="text-gray-400">Developer API</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Row -->
  <section class="py-12 bg-gradient-to-b from-purple-900/10 to-transparent">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/deepkore-lab" class="btn btn-deepkore">Deep Kore Lab</a>
        <a href="/demo" class="btn btn-outline-deepkore">Try the Demo</a>
        <a href="/status" class="btn btn-outline-deepkore">Project Status</a>
        <a href="/ethics" class="btn btn-outline-deepkore">Ethics &amp; Governance</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .text-gradient-deepkore {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #A855F7 0%, #6B21A8 100%);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }

  .btn-deepkore {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #A855F7 0%, #6B21A8 100%);
    color: white;
    padding: 0.75rem 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
    display: inline-block;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .btn-deepkore:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.4);
  }

  .btn-outline-deepkore {
    background: transparent;
    color: #A855F7;
    border: 2px solid #A855F7;
    padding: 0.75rem 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .btn-outline-deepkore:hover {
    background: rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.1);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .stat-card {
    background: rgba(107, 33, 168, 0.1);
    border: 1px solid rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.3);
    padding: 1.25rem 1rem;
    border-radius: 10px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .stat-value {
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #A855F7;
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .stat-label {
    color: rgba(224, 224, 224, 0.65);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  /* Manifesto link card */
  .manifesto-card {
    background: rgba(107, 33, 168, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.35);
    border-radius: 10px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease, background 0.2s ease;
  }

  .manifesto-card:hover {
    background: rgba(107, 33, 168, 0.15);
    border-color: rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.6);
  }

  .manifesto-card-inner {
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .manifesto-card-label {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: #A855F7;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .manifesto-card-title {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #E0E0E0;
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .manifesto-card-sub {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #888;
  }

  /* AIya Tabs */
  .aiya-tabs {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.2);
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }

  .aiya-tab {
    background: transparent;
    border: 1px solid rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.3);
    border-bottom: none;
    color: #A0A0B0;
    padding: 0.55rem 1.1rem;
    border-radius: 6px 6px 0 0;
    font-size: 0.825rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.2s ease;
    position: relative;
    bottom: -2px;
  }

  .aiya-tab:hover {
    color: #A855F7;
    background: rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.08);
  }

  .aiya-tab.active {
    background: rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.15);
    border-color: rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.6);
    border-bottom: 2px solid #0A0E27;
    color: #A855F7;
  }

  .aiya-panel-wrap {
    background: rgba(10, 14, 39, 0.7);
    border: 1px solid rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.2);
    border-top: none;
    border-radius: 0 0 12px 12px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    min-height: 240px;
  }

  .aiya-panel {
    display: none;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .aiya-panel.active {
    display: flex;
  }

  .preview-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    align-self: flex-start;
    background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.12);
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.4);
    color: #00D4FF;
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    padding: 0.18rem 0.7rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .convo-msg {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.25rem;
    max-width: 88%;
  }

  .convo-msg.user {
    align-self: flex-end;
    align-items: flex-end;
  }

  .convo-msg.aiya {
    align-self: flex-start;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .convo-label {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #888;
    padding: 0 0.2rem;
  }

  .aiya-label { color: #A855F7; }

  .convo-bubble {
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    border-radius: 10px;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: #E0E0E0;
  }

  .user-bubble {
    background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.1);
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.3);
    border-top-right-radius: 2px;
    color: #B0EEFF;
  }

  .aiya-bubble {
    background: rgba(107, 33, 168, 0.18);
    border: 1px solid rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.3);
    border-top-left-radius: 2px;
  }

  .governance-note {
    background: rgba(6, 8, 19, 0.7);
    border: 1px solid rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.25);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: #A0A0B8;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.25rem;
    align-self: flex-start;
    max-width: 88%;
  }

  .governance-note-row { display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; }
  .gn-label { color: #A855F7; font-weight: 600; }
  .gn-val { color: #C0C0D0; }

  /* Sandbox */
  .sandbox-prompt-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0.65rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .sandbox-prompt-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }

  .sandbox-btn {
    background: rgba(10, 14, 39, 0.6);
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.3);
    color: #00D4FF;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    cursor: pointer;
    text-align: left;
    transition: all 0.2s ease;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .sandbox-btn:hover {
    background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.1);
    border-color: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.6);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }

  .sandbox-btn.selected {
    background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.15);
    border-color: #00D4FF;
    color: #E0FAFF;
  }

  .sandbox-response-panel {
    background: rgba(10, 14, 39, 0.7);
    border: 1px solid rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.2);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    min-height: 100px;
    color: #E0E0E0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .sandbox-placeholder { color: #666; font-style: italic; }

  /* Governance Panel */
  .governance-panel {
    background: rgba(10, 14, 39, 0.8);
    border: 1px solid rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.3);
    border-radius: 12px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .governance-field {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.8rem 1.25rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.1);
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .governance-field:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .gov-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: #A855F7;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .gov-value { font-size: 0.875rem; color: #C0C0D0; text-align: right; }
  .gov-approved { color: #4ADE80; font-weight: 600; }
  .gov-redirected { color: #F97316; font-weight: 600; }

  .governance-note-box {
    background: rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.06);
    border: 1px solid rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.2);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 0.875rem 1.1rem;
    color: rgba(224, 224, 224, 0.7);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* What Is Real Today */
  .real-today-box {
    border: 1px solid;
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.15rem;
  }

  .real-today-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .real-today-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .real-today-list li {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    padding-left: 1rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .real-today-list li::before {
    content: '-';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    opacity: 0.6;
